I also have some large Fine Art Lino prints. This one is called “Mythical Garden”, it’s 22x30 unframed. 

To make this fine art print I started with hand carving out a large lino block. Then I soaked high quality pure cotton paper in a large bath tub. After the cotton fibers in the paper got loose, I applied acrylic ink using a roller. That’s why in person you can feel the paper raised, which is hard to photograph, but you can notice the “puffy” impression. The final step was to run it through big press and luckily there’s French Press available at a local printmaking studio. 

I created only 10 impressions. Most them already found a home and I have 3 more left. I just reduced the price and they are up for grabs. 

Mirdinara.com/shop

#linoprinting #printmakingart #mirdinara #dinaramirtalipova

Adventure awaits!
Enroute to Aral Sea
Hello, Uzbekistan 💚

I’m returning from an unforgettable life changing trip to the remote areas of Aral Sea where there’s no phone reception, no water or electricity! I’m full of stories, emotions, sketches, experiences and photos. It will take time to process it all and to share. My internet access is limited, I’ll start posting when there’s access.
#aralsea

People of Aral

#mirdinara #dinaramirtalipova #mirdinaraaral #aralsea

Seeing these rusting fishing boats gives me chills! Back in the days Muynak was a thriving fishing town, with a  factory that exported fish and provided jobs. Today it feels more like a ghost town. If you ask the locals if they wish to relocate, they will say that they would rather wish for the waters to return.

Did you know that polar bears are known for their reading habits?! I learned about this fact just recently. I was so excited that I made some free stickers for your water bottles! Grab them, while they last!
Yeah, apparently study shows that polar bears enjoy books about the Arctic, wildlife, or survival in extreme environments. Here are a few book recommendations that a polar bear might find interesting:
"The Call of the Wild" by Jack London, "Arctic Dreams" by Barry Lopez, "Ice Bear: In the Steps of the Polar Bear" by Nicola Davies. 

What else?

I’m so honored that my recent floral packaging design for FIKA confectionery’s Hallongrottor cookies has been accepted to SI66, a juried show at the Society of Illustrators in NY. The exhibit will run Jan 31-Mar 16, and I couldn’t be more thrilled to have my work showcased alongside so many talented artists and designers.

I’m starting my first day in 2024 with a new #Moleskine artbook. It’s not a-painting-a-day sort of challenge, but it’s a more subtle and a gentle way for me to fill it out with moments and emotions throughout the year.
I love the stillness and the quietness of January. It’s like the world is pausing after chaotic December. Hibernation. Permission to procrastinate before it gets busy again. ✨

Hello, 2024!
It just dawned on me, that this year marks a decade since I left my corporate job and began my freelance journey, thanks in large to my dear art agent and mentor Chrystal Falcioni and her art agency @magnetreps. Back in those days the Instagram vibe was totally different – the era of random photos and saturated filters LOL ))) Some folks have remained, others have left, and a few have joined along the way. Perhaps, it’s time for me to re-introduce myself. 

My name is Dinara, I’m a folk artist, deeply fascinated by all things handcrafted, embracing the beauty in imperfections. The term “Folk Art” means the art of people, typically created by amateur self-taught artists, who simply can’t stop painting – that’s me! I can’t stop painting

A few fun facts about me:
- I tend to express my excitement with an excessive use of exclamation points!!!!
- Despite this misleading photo, I’m not a fan of ice-cream, or cold food.
- I have a degree in Computer Science, but instead I’m a self-taught illustrator.
- I work at CIA. I mean I teach at the Cleveland Institute of Art, or CIA. It still cracks me up to say that I work at CIA. 
- I’m an immigrant from Uzbekistan – a country in Central Asia. English is not my language.
- I got to shake Ban Ki-Moon’s hand (a former UN Secretary-General), it was very soft and squishy! 
- I’m an amateur runner. 
- I LOOOOOOVE to travel! Invite me over for your speaking or workshop events and I will have my backpack ready before you can even finish your sentence ))

Big thanks to the amazing art directors who have put up with me all these years, and who have hired me for my quirky art style! I also appreciate the wonderful people who have supported my little online shop. 

What’s next? Currently I’m working on writing and illustrating a children’s book. Plus, there are a few exciting speaking events too!
